docs.lead_paragraph: HALIFAX, N.S., Oct. 24. -- By the death of Miss Mundell of Windsor, Garibaldi's sword now becomes the property of M.A. Goudge. Miss Mundell's brother Joseph took an active part in resisting the subjugation of Uruguay by Rosas, Dictator of Buenos Ayres. Garibaldi was at that time Commander in Chief of the Uruguayan Army and Navy,

docs.lead_paragraph: Prudente de Moraes took his seat yesterday as President of the Republic of Brazil, the third President in succession, but the first elected by the vote of the people. He is a civilian, trained in the law, which he practiced with great success; a Republican of such firm convictions that even under the empire, in private and in public life, he made open profession of his views.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Nov. 22 -- At the last session of Congress a resolution was passed by the Senate requesting the Chairman of the Inter-State Commerce Commission to furnish that body with all the information the commission possessed relating to railroad ownership by foreign Governments. The response of W. R. Morrison, Chairman of the commission, to that resolution has been printed and is being circulated through the Document Room of the Senate.
